SIMPLE: uxorial
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uxorial
<hw>Ux*o"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Uxorious</er>.]</ety> <def>Dotingly fond of, or servilely submissive
to, a wife; uxorious; also, becoming a wife; pertaining to a wife.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The speech [of Zipporah, Ex. iv. 25] is not a speech of reproach
or indignation, but of <qex>uxorial</qex> endearment.</q>
<rj><qau>Geddes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uxoricidal</ent>⟦br⟧
